name: Serendipity-StacyS Edition
description:
Find more exclusively on my patreon!

If you like my work, please consider throwing a tip my way!

This TI is a failure. It doesn't do what I set out to do. I'm not naming it after the person it was modeled after, as it doesn't look anything like them most of the time. The file name is the clue, but it's inconsequential.

It does, however, make for some interesting faces, when used with the right models. It can produce some unique looks in both 2d+ and realistic models. It's a fortunate accident.

I'm uploading the TI at 4100 steps. I might upload some others, as anywhere from 2000 to 5000 steps gives different results. Lower is softer, higher is a little over the top and exaggerated, without being overly overtrained. 4100 seems to produce the best balance and consistency.

I've tried it on a wide variety of models, some work better than others. Only through patience and experimentation can you get this to work for you. Inpainting is pretty much a requirement.
